result.execSummary:
The defendant Dana M White was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Dana M White in court with attorney Daniel Francis Snyder.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 2:15 PM. State - resolved - 16CM80 - amend to county ordinance of obstruction, $300 fine plus costs and on 16CM136, plead g/nc to both and costs only on each count. White and Snyder agree. Court - 16CM80 - amend only count to county ordinance of obstructing, pleads NC, finds G, fine of $300.00 plus costs totalling $582.50 - add to current payment plan. White pleads NC to counts #1 and #2 as alleged on 16CM136. Court has plea questionnaire, goes thru it, finds the defendant has freely, voluntarily and intelligenty waived her constitutional rights by entering her plea and right to JT, accepts plea, adjudges guilty, proceed to sentencing. State - follow joint recommendation. Snyder - follow joint recommendation. White withholds comment. Court sentences the defendant to the following: counts #1 and #2 - costs only - add to current payment plan/CO, submit DNA sample, right to appeal, adjourned.
Final pre-trial on September 30, 2016 at 01:30 pm.
Final pre-trial on September 28, 2016 at 01:15 pm.

Defendant Dana M White in court.  Charles James Simono appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Called at 1:13 PM. Called 16CM80 and 16CM136. State - here for initial appearances on both cases. Court vacates warrant previoulsy entered this morning on 16CM80. State provides defendant with complaint on 16CM136. Court reads charges and penalties on both cases and right to attorney and court appointed attorney. White understands charges and penalties, wants an attorney, asks for SPD. Recess to talk to SPD (1:16 PM). Recalled at 1:42 PM, now appears with Chad Lynch as she qualifies for SPD, there is a conflict with the office on one of the cases, asks for AIA on both cases. Court continues bond on both matters, reinstates signature bond on 16CM80. Lynch will now enters NG pleas to all counts on both cases. Court accepts pleas, continues bond on 16CM136 and reinstates signature bond on 16CM80  Final pre-trial scheduled for September 28, 2016 at 01:15 pm.
